						<div class="postbody">I personally wouldn't charge for a Nes homebrew ROM because I know not a lot of people would buy it to justify charging for it, meaning I made it for some other reason than profit. At most I'd charge for a physical cartridge (because that's a lot of work/materials) but I'd still give the ROM away for free. You know, thinking about it, I'd do the ROM with a &quot;pay what you want&quot; price, starting from FREE. But that's me of course, I can understand someone charging whatever they want.</div>

					
